Match simulation harness coverage
=================================

The Python tests exercise the deterministic match simulator found under
``tools/tests/match_sim``. In addition to the baseline duel and overtime
scenarios, the suite now bundles ``factory_cvars.json`` to validate the
behaviour of factory-related CVars:

* ``test_factory_loadout_toggle_updates_inventory`` toggles the active
  loadout metadata and ensures bots spawn with the expected ammo and
  inventory stacks, while verifying per-bot overrides remain intact.
* ``test_factory_spawn_delays_emit_client_spawn_events`` checks that
  warmup and live ``ClientSpawn`` events are delayed according to the
  configured factory schedule.
* ``test_factory_item_flags_control_drop_behaviour`` flips the drop and
  bounce flags and compares the resulting item timelines with the golden
  expectations stored in ``tests/expectations/match_sim_factory_items.expect``.

The new scenario is also registered inside ``tests/run_harnesses.py`` so
CI artefact generation captures the extended coverage.
